William A Lipphardt was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means William A Lipphardt was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Waiver of Extradition and Order of Remand

Def appears in custody & w/Atty Alyssa Armbrust State Public Defenders Office.  Atty Peter John Cannon for State.  Clerk: EZ.  (16CF14)  Court finds there is a warrant signed by a judge in Iowa.  Court adjourns to determine if Governor's warrant will be issued.  Counsel advises the defendant is willing to sign waiver.  Case recalled at 3:58 p.m.  Counsel advises the defendant wishes to waive extradition.  State not issuing any additional charges at this point.  Court executes order of remand.
Extradition - fugitive from State of Iowa, to-wit: County of Cerro Gordo for three counts of forgery
